column5: Ended up going to Anishinabi on the weekend.Smooth ride in on tge groomed trail.12 fisherman in camp.Two different parties in 2 cabins plus 7 of us.Fun time.Everybody fishing all over the main lake and everybody catching fish.Lots of lake trout and a lot of ling.Could not have had better weather in around the 0c range.Cleaned a lot if trout and some ling for a huge fish fry Saturday night.Got out early enough on Sunday to head home and catch the Super Bowl.Some stayed at camp to catch game there.Another great adventure.Trout were mainly down in a 100 ft of water and white tubes and vibratos were working very well
Nice fish John. Fresh plate of fish sure looks good at this point of the winter.
Everyone ènjoyed to meal.wayne did his famous trout in 7 layers of tin foil in the fireplace.that was awesome to.
Might add we ate some ling to and everybody seemed to enjoy them.just hate touching them.
Hey John, when did you say the show with you and Troy Lindner fishing Anishinabi was going to air? Have to record it.
From what i heard it will be in march.ill see if i can fìnd a date.it will be on the Ontario Experience.
